@{
    ViewBag.Title = "User Groups";
}

<div class="copy-block row">
    <div class="large-12 columns">
        <h4 id="user-groups">User Groups</h4>
    </div>
    <div class="small-12 columns">
        <p>
            Community is a really important part of the DDD Sydney ethos and we couldn't do what we do without the support of many different User Groups around Sydney.
        </p>
        <p>
            So if you've got a spare evening, head on down to a User Group, hang out with other like-minded people and keep the community spirit going.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="small-12 columns">
        <h5 id="altnet">ALT.NET Sydney (<a href="https://www.meetup.com/Sydney-Alt-Net/" title="altnet website">Website</a>)</h5>
        <p>
            ALT.NET Sydney is one of the longest running Sydney .NET user groups, and focuses on the non-Microsoft world of being a .NET developer. Across the months there are talks on everything from DevOps to Xamarin, Cloud to browsers and everything in between.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="small-12 column">
        <h5 id="girls-dotnet">Girls .Net (<a href="https://www.meetup.com/Girls-NET/">Website</a>)</h5>
        <p>
            Girls .Net is a place for passionate female .net developers to learn from each other's experiences, socialise and network with a like-minded female in the industry. Girls .Net provides a safe space for female developers to have chances to practice their presentation skills and foster some new thought leaders.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="small-12 column">
        <h5 id="girls-dotnet">Girls Geek Sydney (<a href="https://www.meetup.com/Girl-Geek-Sydney/">Website</a>)</h5>
        <p>
            Girl Geek Sydney is a volunteer run community group focusing on promoting and engaging women in technology in Sydney. Girl Geek Sydney has its regular meetups and also organises She Hacks all-women hackathon.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="small-12 columns">
        <h5 id="sitecore">Sydney Sitecore User Group (<a href="https://www.meetup.com/Sydney-Sitecore-User-Group/" title="sitecore sydney website">Website</a>)</h5>
        <p>
            The Sydney Sitecore User Group meets monthly for networking, learning. The user group is open to anyone using or considering <a href="http://www.sitecore.net/" target="_blank">the Sitecore Experience Platform</a>, or who has an interest in .NET CMS platforms, regardless of technical proficiency. Programmers, marketers, content authors, CMS users and others are all welcome.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="small-12 columns">
        <h5 id="umbraco">Sydney Umbraco User Group (<a href="https://www.meetup.com/Sydney-Umbraco-Meetup/" title="umbraco sydney website">Website</a>)</h5>
        <p>
            Umbraco Sydney is a bi-monthly user group focusing on the is a popular Open Source content management system. Umbraco prides itself on being all about the community. They hold an annual Festival rather than a Conference in Denmark (obviously a bit of a hike for us in Sydney!) which is all about having fun as a web developer.
        </p>
    </div>

</div>
